SIMPLE: dastard
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dastard
<hw>Das"tard</hw> <pr>(d⟦acr⟧s"t⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Prob. from Icel. <ets>d⟦ae⟧str</ets> exhausted. breathless, p. p.
of <ets>d⟦ae⟧sa</ets> to groan, lose one's breath; cf. <ets>dasask</ets>
to become exhausted, and E. <ets>daze</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who meanly
shrinks from danger; an arrant coward; a poltroon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You are all recreants and <qex>dashtards</qex>, and delight to
live in slavery to the nobility.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dastard</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dastard
<hw>Das"tard</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Meanly shrinking from danger;
cowardly; dastardly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Their <xex>dastard</xex> souls.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dastard</ent>⟦br⟧

